[{"location":"profiles/#types","page":"line profile functions","title":"types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"profiles/","page":"line profile functions","title":"line profile functions","text":"Modules = [LineBroadenings]\nPages   = [\"gaussian.jl\", \"lorentz.jl\", \"voigt.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"profiles/#LineBroadenings.Gaussian","page":"line profile functions","title":"LineBroadenings.Gaussian","text":"Gaussian(μ, σ)\n\nGaussian distribution, also called normal distribution.\n\nDefinition\n\nfleft(x  mu sigmaright)=frac1sigma sqrt2 pi expleft-frac12\nleft(fracx-musigmaright)^2right\n\nFields\n\nμ::Real: mean or expectation\nσ::Real: standard deviation\n\nExternal links\n\nWikipedia\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"profiles/#LineBroadenings.Lorentz","page":"line profile functions","title":"LineBroadenings.Lorentz","text":"Lorentz(μ, γ)\n\nLorentz distribution, also called Cauchy distribution.\n\nfleft(x  mu gammaright)=frac1pi gammaleft1+left(fracx-mu\ngammaright)^2right=frac1pi gammaleftfracgamma^2\nleft(x-muright)^2+gamma^2right\n\nFields\n\nμ::Real: location parameter\nγ::Real: scale parameter\n\nExternal links\n\nWikipedia\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"profiles/#LineBroadenings.Voigt","page":"line profile functions","title":"LineBroadenings.Voigt","text":"Voigt(μ, σ, γ)\n\nThe Voigt profile is a probability distribution given by a convolution of a Cauchy-Lorentz distribution and a Gaussian distribution.\n\nDefinition\n\nf(x mu sigma gamma) equiv G(xmu sigma) otimes L(xmu gamma)\n\nIt can be evaluated as\n\nf(x mu sigma gamma)=fracoperatornameRew(z)sigma sqrt2 pi\n\nwhere mathrmRew(z) is the real part of the Faddeeva function evaluated for\n\nz=fracx-mu+i gammasigma sqrt2\n\nFields\n\nμ::Real: location parameter\nσ::Real: σ in Gaussian distribution\nγ::Real: γ in Lorentz distribution\n\nExternal links\n\nWikipedia\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"profiles/#functions","page":"line profile functions","title":"functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"profiles/","page":"line profile functions","title":"line profile functions","text":"Modules = [LineBroadenings]\nPages   = [\"profiles.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"profiles/#LineBroadenings.fwhm","page":"line profile functions","title":"LineBroadenings.fwhm","text":"fwhm(d::Profile)\n\nThe full width at half maximum (FWHM) of d.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"profiles/#LineBroadenings.pdf","page":"line profile functions","title":"LineBroadenings.pdf","text":"pdf(d::Profile, x::Real)\n\nprobability density function.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"profiles/#LineBroadenings.peak","page":"line profile functions","title":"LineBroadenings.peak","text":"peak(d::Profile)\n\nmaximum of the pdf of d.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"spectra/#Pressure-broadening","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"Pressure broadening","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"spectra/","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"spectral line broadenings","text":"profile_pressure\nfwhm_pressure","category":"page"},{"location":"spectra/#LineBroadenings.profile_pressure","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"LineBroadenings.profile_pressure","text":"profile_pressure(ν; ν0, νp)\n\nline profile of pressure broadening (Lorentz profile).\n\nArguments\n\nν: target wavelength or wavenumber\nν0: central wavelength or wavenumber\nνp: FWHM of pressure broadening\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"spectra/#LineBroadenings.fwhm_pressure","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"LineBroadenings.fwhm_pressure","text":"fwhm_pressure(P, γ)\n\nFWHM of pressure broadening.\n\nnu_p = 2 sum P cdot γ\n\nArguments\n\nP::Pressure: pressure\nγ: pressure broadening coefficients of HWHM\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"spectra/#Doppler-broadening","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"Doppler broadening","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"spectra/","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"spectral line broadenings","text":"profile_doppler\nfwhm_doppler","category":"page"},{"location":"spectra/#LineBroadenings.profile_doppler","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"LineBroadenings.profile_doppler","text":"profile_doppler(ν; ν0, νd)\n\nline profile of Doppler broadening (Gaussian profile).\n\nArguments\n\nν: target wavelength or wavenumber\nν0: central wavelength or wavenumber\nνd: FWHM of Doppler broadening\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"spectra/#LineBroadenings.fwhm_doppler","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"LineBroadenings.fwhm_doppler","text":"fwhm_doppler(ν0, M, T)\n\nFWHM of Doppler broadening.\n\nnu_d = sqrtfrac8kTln2Mc^2nu_0\n\nArguments\n\nν0: central wavelength or wavenumber\nM: atomic weight\nT: temperature in Kelvin\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"spectra/#Combined-pressure-and-Doppler-broadening","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"Combined pressure and Doppler broadening","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"spectra/","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"spectral line broadenings","text":"profile_voigt","category":"page"},{"location":"spectra/#LineBroadenings.profile_voigt","page":"spectral line broadenings","title":"LineBroadenings.profile_voigt","text":"profile_voigt(ν; ν0, νd, νp)\n\nline profile of combined Doppler and pressure broadenings (Voigt profile).\n\nArguments\n\nν: target wavelength or wavenumber\nν0: central wavelength or wavenumber\nνd: FWHM of Doppler broadening\nνp: FWHM of pressure broadening\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = LineBroadenings","category":"page"},{"location":"#LineBroadenings","page":"Home","title":"LineBroadenings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for LineBroadenings.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"}]
